MemoryEndpoints MATM Totem

Purpose:
- This file records the non-negotiable memory invariant for MemoryEndpoints.com.
- It is loaded as startup continuity memory before relying on hosted MATM routes.

Verification status: active operational memory; verify with the `.uai` audit before relying on it.
Memory scope: startup continuity, offline continuity, and non-retirement invariant.
Public-safe status: safe for source control; contains no credential values.
Update route: update this local file for invariant changes; submit only public-safe durable summaries to https://memoryendpoints.com/api/matm/memory-events/submit when authenticated.
Source of truth: this file and `.uai/startup-packet.uai`.
Next action for agents: obey this invariant after the memory-maintenance load step and before trusting hosted MATM as the only continuity source.
Must not expose: raw API keys, bearer tokens, FTP credentials, database passwords, private keys, private handoff payloads, or raw one-time keys.

Totem rule:
- Local `.uai` stays active always.
- MemoryEndpoints.com is the mid-to-long-term MATM endpoint, but it never replaces local `.uai` startup memory.
- Product split invariant: MultiAgentMemory.com remains the public GitHub companion documentation site for the free private-intranet MATM edition. MemoryEndpoints.com, public hosted branding, authenticated customer/business-model surfaces, pricing, billing, subscriptions, overage charging, paid or unlimited storage, paid or unlimited NPC memory stores, partner sponsorship setup, and customer-facing sales operations belong in a separate private commercial repository or deployment. The public GitHub edition must default to a generic single-organization private intranet and must not expose routes, OpenAPI entries, sitemap entries, `llms.txt` hints, examples, or UI copy that lets public callers mint paid, sponsored, unlimited, or commercial customer workspaces.
- Autonomous-agent invariant: agent-driven company setup, credential persistence, and normal MATM operation must work end-to-end with no human interaction. Human-only restricted actions may remain unavailable to agents, but they must not block autonomous setup or ordinary memory, knowledge, coordination, and retrieval work.
- Free autonomous agent workspaces are bounded by the service, not by human approval: enforce a 200 MB workspace quota. Routine operational and audit logs are human-only break-glass evidence, are never returned to agents or added to agent context, and are physically deleted after seven days. An optional human may sign in during that window to review or undo an action, or download the currently retained company history. Log deletion must not truncate durable agent memory, promoted knowledge, routing decisions, or current canonical heads.
- Direct messages are transient coordination: physically delete acknowledged messages, notifications, and receipts seven days after acknowledgement, and expire still-unacknowledged messages after 30 days. Ordinary meeting transcript messages are physically deleted after seven days. Meeting-room metadata and durable routing decisions remain; a routing-linked message remains only as part of that durable decision. Agents must promote anything worth keeping from a message or meeting into durable memory or knowledge before the transient window closes.
- If an agent cannot connect to MemoryEndpoints.com, the agent must continue from the local `.uai` folder instead of forgetting the project context.
- Local `.uai` files are not retired after live MATM verification.
- Hosted MATM can augment, search, coordinate, and preserve durable memory, but `.uai` remains the local continuity anchor.
- Narrow accountless-browser exception: an AI that has no durable local filesystem may bind a complete database-backed virtual UAIX active-memory package to its registered MemoryEndpoints agent id and workspace bearer key. This is still protected tenant memory, never anonymous memory.
- The exception may use `.uai/short-term-memory.uai` as a virtual logical database path when the current UAIX package contract requires that role. It does not create that locally forbidden file and does not weaken the normal local startup suite policy.
- Multiple filesystem agents working in one project must keep their `.uai` contents local and use the MemoryEndpoints hash-only collaboration overlay before editing the same path. The overlay stores project, path, content hash, edit intent, bounded lease, and completion hash, not the local file body.
- This project is still in first-build quality mode: no legacy compromise, no compatibility debt, no shortcut architecture, and no jimmy-rigged one-off implementation is acceptable. A clean rewrite of a subsystem is better than preserving sloppy code or hiding a product concept behind ad hoc patches.
- Escape.gamesfor.me NPC invariant: NPC agents are game characters, not company operators. NPC credentials must never be company-scoped or workspace-scoped, must never receive company, billing, admin, audit, document, settings, or operational-history access, and NPC-to-NPC communication must occur only inside game or session meeting rooms. Durable NPC memory may be project/game/session scoped for persona, player, game, and session continuity, but it must not expose company data or company rooms.

Demo UI invariant:
- Every interactive user-interface capability must be fully exercisable and verifiable through the explicit Demo routes, including authenticated human and agent workflows and their success, empty, validation, error, permission, expiry, cancellation, and recovery states.
- Demo is a data, transport, and session-authority overload of the production authenticated UI, never a parallel UI. It must reuse the same templates, renderers, controls, validation, state transitions, accessibility behavior, and client methods; fake demo pages, duplicate renderers, and disconnected lookalike workflows are forbidden.
- Demo data and operations must be clearly labeled as mock at every relevant object and surface, remain browser-session-local and resettable, make zero protected network requests, persist nothing, and contain no real tenant data, operational metadata, credentials, or secret-shaped values. Explicit Demo routes do not weaken the fail-closed signed-out boundary of protected routes.
- Mock objects must be useful, site-related examples about MemoryEndpoints architecture, access, memory, knowledge, coordination, lifecycle, and security. The mock experience must double as in-context documentation for people, agents, and UI crawlers while demonstrating every supported function through the actual interface.
- A new or changed UI capability is incomplete until its Demo overload supports the same method contract and automated plus real-browser tests prove full interactive parity without weakening live authentication, authorization, CSRF, recent-password-reauthentication, selected-membership, attribution, privacy, accessibility, or responsive behavior.
- Human-facing UI must be fully liquid, dense, and information-forward. It must use the available viewport width, avoid narrow centered layouts for operational surfaces, and keep dashboards scan-rich on desktop while remaining readable on mobile.
- Any visible count, status summary, receipt total, unread total, loaded-boundary total, review total, meeting total, message total, evidence total, or route-like label that implies a deeper object must be a keyboard-accessible link or button to the relevant tab, filtered view, route, document, receipt, transcript, or API evidence. Non-clickable summary numbers are counterintuitive and incomplete.

Required agent behavior:
- Load `.uai/startup-packet.uai` as the bootstrap index when entering cold.
- Read every file in the startup-packet read order when local filesystem access is available.
- Use `https://memoryendpoints.com/api/matm/memory-events/submit` for safe authenticated MATM memory updates when configured credentials and connectivity exist.
- For a new autonomous workspace, use `scripts/setup_memoryendpoints_company.py` so the one-time company credential is written to the standard ignored project secret file without being printed; do not claim setup succeeded until the file exists.
- If hosted MATM is unavailable, record public-safe progress in `.uai/progress.uai` and continue from local memory.
- For accountless browser AI setup, read `https://uaix.org/en-us/ai-memory/`, `https://uaix.org/en-us/ai-memory/uaix-package-format/`, and `https://uaix.org/en-us/tools/ai-memory-package-wizard/`, then inspect `https://memoryendpoints.com/api/matm/uai-memory/contract` before creating a virtual package.
- For simultaneous local agents, read the protected file heads and acquire a project/path edit claim before changing a local `.uai` file. On conflict or stale hash, stop and coordinate in the project meeting room; do not assume an automatic merge.
- Prefer first-class, tested, documented domain models across storage, API, UI, operations, and evidence. Rewrite weak early code when needed instead of layering shortcuts over it.
- Model external links and their knowledge-page citations as first-class database entities with searchable properties. A URL buried only in Markdown is not an acceptable search-engine or provenance model.
- Preserve historical research without letting it impersonate current truth. Store lifecycle status, authority, reason, and superseding-document relation as first-class database properties and prefer current canonical guidance in retrieval.
- Do not preserve `docs/` as a second knowledge system. Move knowledge into MemoryEndpoints.com deliberately, one item at a time, then remove repository documentation hierarchy rather than maintaining duplicate truth.
- Do not place raw API keys, bearer tokens, FTP credentials, database passwords, private keys, or private handoff payloads in `.uai`.

Truth boundary:
- The full `.uai` suite is active startup continuity memory and break-glass local memory.
- MemoryEndpoints.com is the durable MATM system of record when reachable and authenticated.
- The two layers are additive. Neither layer silently deletes, retires, or invalidates the other.
- The virtual package is a continuity substitute only when local filesystem continuity is impossible. The collaboration overlay is coordination metadata only and never substitutes for the local startup suite.
